From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v53 - inject TX SETUP + SETUP_VSEMPH before ENABLE on Liverpool DP

The v52 trace (after patch 0026 floored dig_connector->dp_clock=270000
and dp_lane_count=4) showed the encoder side now gets correct values:

  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0f (SETUP)        ... dp_clk=270000 dp_lanes=4
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x10 (PANEL_MODE)   ... dp_clk=270000 dp_lanes=4
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0d (DP_VIDEO_ON)  ... dp_clk=270000 dp_lanes=4

But the TRANSMITTER side runs only DISABLE → ENABLE, with no SETUP
between:

  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=0 (DISABLE) ... dp_clk=270000 dp_lanes=4
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=1 (ENABLE)  ... dp_clk=270000 dp_lanes=4

(The "lane_num=0 lane_set=0x00" reading in v52 was misleading — for
crev=5 those function parameters are not used by ENABLE. Inspecting
atombios_encoders.c:1037-1091, the v5 ENABLE case sets
args.v5.ucLaneNum from dp_lane_count and args.v5.usSymClock from
dp_clock, both of which are now correct via the v52 floor. So ENABLE's
args struct is correct on its own.)

The actual sequence gap: stock CIK DP path runs
ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_SETUP (10) and ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_SETUP_VSEMPH
(11) inside amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train — the trainer invokes them
during clock recovery and channel-equalization phases to program TX
voltage swing and pre-emphasis per lane. Patch 0006 makes link_train
early-return for Liverpool/Gladius (because the kernel's clock-recovery
loop times out on the fake-DP MN864729 link), so SETUP and SETUP_VSEMPH
never run. The TX gets ENABLE'd with no prior SETUP — ATOM bytecode for
ENABLE may rely on TX state that SETUP would have established.

This patch (v53) does two things:

1. In amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig (atombios_encoders.c:1356), at
   the point where the bare ENABLE call lives, prepend two new calls
   for the Liverpool/Gladius DP path:

     ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_SETUP        (10)  with lane_set=0
     ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_SETUP_VSEMPH (11)  with lane_set=0

   lane_set=0 is the first training voltage/preemphasis level (DPCD
   "voltage swing 0, pre-emphasis 0"). For an internal hardwired
   bridge link, that should be sufficient; the bridge handles the
   real receiver-side training internally over its ICC command queue.

2. In amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_transmitter (right before the
   final amdgpu_atom_execute_table call), add a "final args" trace for
   crev=5 and crev=6 that prints the actual struct fields ATOM
   bytecode receives:

     args.v5.ucAction
     args.v5.ucPhyId           (which UNIPHY: A/B/C/D/E/F)
     args.v5.usSymClock        (link symbol clock — from dp_clock)
     args.v5.ucLaneNum         (lane count — from dp_lane_count)
     args.v5.ucConnObjId       (connector object ID)
     args.v5.ucDigMode         (encoder mode: DP/HDMI/etc)
     args.v5.asConfig.ucHPDSel (HPD pin)
     args.v5.ucDigEncoderSel   (which DIG: 1<<dig_encoder)
     args.v5.ucDPLaneSet       (voltage swing/pre-emphasis level)

   This confirms whether SETUP/SETUP_VSEMPH/ENABLE all see coherent PHY
   and lane state, and lets us spot any case-block bug where one action
   leaves a field at a wrong default.

Patch 0006 (skip-DP-link-train) stays in place. We are NOT enabling the
full DP trainer here — that would re-introduce the clock-recovery
timeout on the bridge's fake DPCD. We're just running the source-side
ATOM actions that the trainer would have done first.

Expected next-boot trace markers:

  ps4_atom: floor dig_connector dp_clock=270000 dp_lane_count=4    (v52)
  ps4_atom: AdjustDisplayPll v1.3 OUT r=0 freq=270000              (v47)
  ps4_atom: SetPixelClock IN ... pll=1 ...                         (v49)
  ps4_atom: SetPixelClock OUT r=0
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0c ... dp_clk=270000 dp_lanes=4
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=0 (DISABLE)
  ps4_atom: dig_tx final v5: action=0 ...
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0f (SETUP)
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x10 (PANEL_MODE)
  ps4_atom: forcing TX SETUP + SETUP_VSEMPH before ENABLE          (v53)
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=10 (SETUP) ...                            (v53)
  ps4_atom: dig_tx final v5: action=10 phyId=0x?? symClk=27000 laneNum=4 ...
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=11 (SETUP_VSEMPH) ...                    (v53)
  ps4_atom: dig_tx final v5: action=11 ... dpLaneSet=0x00
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=1 (ENABLE)
  ps4_atom: dig_tx final v5: action=1 phyId=0x?? symClk=27000 laneNum=4 ...
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0d (DP_VIDEO_ON)
  ps4_bridge_enable: cq_exec=20 (with the 3-s wait collapsed)

Outcomes:

  - Bridge cq_wait_set 3-s hang collapses to <500 ms + screen lights up
    → done. v47/v49/v52/v53 are the keepers.
  - "final v5" trace shows phyId/digEncSel inconsistencies between
    SETUP and ENABLE → v54 fixes the inconsistent field.
  - Trace shows SETUP/VSEMPH/ENABLE all coherent but bridge still hangs
    → next test is controlled DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN1 source-side
    pulse (without the kernel's DPCD-driven recovery loop) — keep
    patch 0006 active and call setup_dig_encoder with
    ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN1 manually before
    DP_VIDEO_ON.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_encoders.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_encoders.c
@@ -1161,6 +1161,29 @@
 			action, frev, crev, amdgpu_encoder->encoder_id,
 			dig_encoder, pll_id, is_dp, dp_clock, dp_lane_count,
 			lane_num, lane_set, connector_object_id, hpd_id);
+	/* v53: final-args dump for crev=5/6 — show what actually gets handed
+	 * to ATOM bytecode after the case-block populated the args struct.
+	 * Liverpool's PS4 VBIOS uses crev=5 typically. Useful to confirm
+	 * v52's connector floor propagated to args.v5.ucLaneNum/usSymClock
+	 * and to diagnose whether SETUP/SETUP_VSEMPH/ENABLE actions all see
+	 * the same coherent PHY/DigMode/HPDSel/DigEncoderSel state. */
+	if ((adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+	    && frev == 1) {
+		if (crev == 5)
+			pr_info("ps4_atom: dig_tx final v5: action=%u phyId=0x%02x symClk=%u laneNum=%u connObj=0x%02x digMode=%u hpdSel=%u digEncSel=0x%02x dpLaneSet=0x%02x\n",
+				args.v5.ucAction, args.v5.ucPhyId,
+				le16_to_cpu(args.v5.usSymClock),
+				args.v5.ucLaneNum, args.v5.ucConnObjId,
+				args.v5.ucDigMode, args.v5.asConfig.ucHPDSel,
+				args.v5.ucDigEncoderSel, args.v5.ucDPLaneSet);
+		else if (crev == 6)
+			pr_info("ps4_atom: dig_tx final v6: action=%u phyId=0x%02x symClk=%u laneNum=%u connObj=0x%02x digMode=%u hpdSel=%u digEncSel=0x%02x dpLaneSet=0x%02x\n",
+				args.v6.ucAction, args.v6.ucPhyId,
+				le32_to_cpu(args.v6.ulSymClock),
+				args.v6.ucLaneNum, args.v6.ucConnObjId,
+				args.v6.ucDigMode, args.v6.ucHPDSel,
+				args.v6.ucDigEncoderSel, args.v6.ucDPLaneSet);
+	}
 	amdgpu_atom_execute_table(adev->mode_info.atom_context, index, (uint32_t *)&args, sizeof(args));
 }

@@ -1353,6 +1376,29 @@
 				amdgpu_dig_connector->edp_on = true;
 			}
 		}
+		/* v53 (PS4 Liverpool/Gladius): stock CIK DP path runs SETUP and
+		 * SETUP_VSEMPH from inside amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train (the
+		 * trainer adjusts voltage swing per-lane), but patch 0006 makes
+		 * link_train early-return for Liverpool. Without those actions
+		 * the TX state is never explicitly programmed before ENABLE
+		 * turns on the PHY — ATOM bytecode for ENABLE may rely on TX
+		 * state established by SETUP. v52 trace showed only DISABLE→
+		 * ENABLE in the modeset path. Inject SETUP + SETUP_VSEMPH (with
+		 * a default lane_set=0 = first training voltage/preemphasis
+		 * level) before ENABLE so the TX gets fully configured. */
+		{
+			struct amdgpu_device *adev = drm_to_adev(encoder->dev);
+			if ((adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL ||
+			     adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS) &&
+			    ENCODER_MODE_IS_DP(amdgpu_atombios_encoder_get_encoder_mode(encoder)) &&
+			    connector) {
+				pr_info("ps4_atom: forcing TX SETUP + SETUP_VSEMPH before ENABLE\n");
+				amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_transmitter(encoder,
+						ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_SETUP, 0, 0);
+				amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_transmitter(encoder,
+						ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_SETUP_VSEMPH, 0, 0);
+			}
+		}
 		/* enable the transmitter */
 		amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_transmitter(encoder,
 						       ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_ENABLE,
